    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
      <body> 
        <div rend="parallel">
            <p xml:id="Aink410-kilavi">
                kaṭimaṉaic ceṉṟa cevili talaimakaṉum talaimakaḷum putalvaṉoṭu pāṭal kēṭṭiruntamai kaṇṭu taṉṉuḷḷē uvantu colliyatu.
            </p>
            <p xml:lang="en">
                Having been to the marriage house, the foster mother, after hearing the singing of the hero and the heroine along with the son and seeing their existence, spoke [this] about them joyously to herself. 
            </p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
                <lg xml:id="Aink410">
            <l>mālai muṉṟiṟ kuṟuṅkāṭ ṭiṉṉakai</l>
            <l>maṉaiyō ṭuṇaivi yākap putalvaṉ</l>
            <l>mārpi ṉūru makiḻnakai yiṉpap</l>
            <l>poḻutiṟ kottaṉṟu maṉṉē</l>
            <l>meṉpiṇit tamma pāṇaṉa tiyāḻē.</l>
          </lg>
          <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l>Oh, the bard's lute - softly enchanting<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">I take <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">piṇi-ttal</foreign> in the sense of 'to ensnare' to 'to bind'. I think context of a lute, I think this refers to the music carrying a bewtiching quality, on account of its beauty.</note> -</l>
<l>is perfectly suited to the joyful time of laughing pleasure</l>
    <l>when the son crawled on [his] chest</l>
    <l>while the smiling wife, [his] companion,</l> 
    <l>was on the low cot in the frontyard in the evening.</l> 
    
          </lg>
        </div>
      </body>
    </text>
